sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K633014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: AraC+Pbad promoter+RBS+signal peptide phoA+Cellulase+Linker+estA membrane protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The composite part includes a functional expression vector for autotransporter membrane protein estA, with a linker united to a cellulase, attached to a membrane signaling peptide. This was our final construct missing a terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ricardo Camilo Chavez Martinez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13458
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: promoter C and arabinose C operon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PC and AraC from the AraBAD operator. PC and AraC are on the complementary strand, reading right to left.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Michener

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K633002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We used Rybosome Binding Site BBa_B0034 designed by by Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr, evaluated by Warsaw's 2010 team. we added membrane protein signal peptide phoA and cellulase immediately next to it
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ricardo Camilo Chavez Martinez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since this part is supposed to be attached to part BBa_K633001 in order to geerate part BBa_K633014, we had to begin with both the signal peptide and then the extracelular domain, which is located on the N terminal side of the polypeptide chain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K633001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We used a linker attached to a protein membrane "estA"
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ricardo Camilo Chavez Martinez
